Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to de Kock, out Caught by Sarfaraz Khan!! Excellent catch! Was dipping on Sarfaraz who timed his dive forward well to take a sharp catch at short third man. Credit to Kuldeep too, didn't get intimidated by the boundaries and had the courage to toss this one up, loopy leg break, inviting de Kock to go for the big shot and the South African couldn't resist. Tried to go inside out over cover, only to get a thick outside edge. A terrific innings nevertheless, he's put Lucknow on the doorsteps of victory. de Kock c Sarfaraz Khan b Kuldeep Yadav 80(52) [4s-9 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Lalit Yadav to Lewis, out Caught by Kuldeep Yadav!! The matchup card works right for DC! Lalit was on primarily due to the two left-handers batting in tandem, neither of whom are really that efficient against off spin. He kept plugging away on a length, hoping for one of the duo to go across the line on this two-paced deck. Lewis is the one to walk into the trap, looking to pull across the line but the extra bounce does him in. Skews it straight up towards the mid-on region where Kuldeep is ready, having trekked backwards from mid-wicket. Lewis c Kuldeep Yadav b Lalit Yadav 5(13)

Commentary Text: Lalit Yadav to Lewis, leg byes, 2 runs, DC burn their final review! A desperate one this, because it was the slider and always looked to be going down leg. Lewis missed the sweep and got struck in front of leg stump. But the appeal from all the DC players, including skipper Pant was so vociferous and they perhaps felt it was really close. In the end, it's clearly missing leg stump on ball tracking and they don't have reviews left now

Commentary Text: Kuldeep Yadav to Rahul, out Caught by Prithvi Shaw at long-off!! There's the first breakthrough. Rahul waltzes down the pitch, looks to loft a maximum straight down the ground, but doesn't get anywhere near the pitch of the delivery.
